1. ACTION PLAN OVERVIEW

Purpose

This Year 2 Action Plan builds on Year 1 (2025-2026) successes and accelerates Brandix Strategic Plan 2025-2030 implementation with scaled initiatives, expanded scope, and increased ambition across all strategic pillars.

Year 1 Achievements Summary

✓ Renewable Energy: Achieved 55% (15 MW solar installed)
✓ Sustainable Water Mix: Achieved 32% (5 facilities with RWH)
✓ Sustainable Materials: Achieved 50% (6,000 tons sustainable materials)
✓ Waste Recycling: Achieved 92% (zero landfill waste)
✓ Digital Integration: Achieved 50% (8 production lines)
✓ Women in Management: Achieved 28% (18 promotions)
✓ Community Beneficiaries: Reached 450,000 people
✓ Zero fatalities and high-consequence injuries maintained

Year 2 Strategic Priorities

- Scale successful Year 1 pilots to full deployment
- Accelerate digital transformation across operations
- Expand renewable energy infrastructure (Phase 2)
- Deepen community impact and social programs
- Advance toward Net Zero Carbon targets
- Strengthen innovation pipeline and R&D capabilities

Year 2 Targets

- Renewable Energy: Increase from 55% to 65%
- Sustainable Water Mix: Increase from 32% to 38%
- Sustainable Materials: Increase from 50% to 58%
- Waste Recycling: Maintain 92%+, target 94%
- Digital Integration: Increase from 50% to 60%
- Women in Management: Increase from 28% to 32%
- Virtual Sampling: Increase from 40% to 60%
- Community Beneficiaries: 550,000 direct beneficiaries
- Innovations Launched: 15 innovations (from 5 in Year 1)

Budget Allocation Year 2

Total Budget: $32.5 million (19% of projected revenue)

- Environmental: $14M (43%)
- Innovation & Digital: $9.5M (29%)
- People & Social: $5M (15%)
